OL,3,CThousands of Next retailer workers win
OL,4,Clandmark equal pay claim
OL,6,FNext argued during the tribunal that
OL,7,Fthe wage difference between sales
OL,8,Fconsultants and warehouse operatives
OL,9,Fwas due to the different "market
OL,10,Frates" for these roles and was
OL,11,Fnecessary for the "viability" of the
OL,12,Fbusiness.
OL,14,FThe tribunal found that the pay
OL,15,Fdifference between the two roles was
OL,16,Fnot due to "direct discrimination" or
OL,17,Fthe "conscious or subconscious
OL,18,Finfluence of gender" on pay decisions,
OL,19,Fbut was instead driven by efforts to
OL,20,F"reduce cost and enhance profit."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
